=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Succinic acid → diethyl succinate by Fischer esterification (EtOH, H+) | Step 2: Self-Claisen/Dieckmann condensation of 2 equiv diethyl succinate with NaOEt/EtOH, then H3O+ → diethyl succinylsuccinate (the symmetric cyclohexane-1,4-dione-2,5-dicarboxylate) | Step 3: Deprotonate both C-2/C-5 methines and alkylate with 2 equiv MeI (e.g., NaOEt or LDA, then MeI) → diethyl 2,5-dimethylsuccinylsuccinate | Step 4: Hydrolyze both ethyl esters to the diacid (aq. base, then acid workup) → 2,5-dimethylcyclohexane-1,4-dione-2,5-dicarboxylic acid | Step 5: Convert the diacid to the allyl diester with allyl bromide and base (or via acid chloride then allyl alcohol) → diallyl 2,5-dimethylcyclohexane-1,4-dione-2,5-dicarboxylate, i.e. O=C(CC1(C)C(OCC=C)=O)C(C(OCC=C)=O)(C)CC1=O

